Below are 10 suggestions to help you among with the pros and cons of each:

1. Website designer

   Pros – highly creative, potentially high-demand skillset, flexibility in choosing clients
   Cons – may require a significant amount of practice and investment in software

2. Freelance writer/blogger

   Pros – expressive outlet, ability to work remotely/choose your own schedule and topics
   Cons – often required to begin with lower pay until an established portfolio is built up
  
3. Online tutor/teacher

   Pros - great way to share knowledge/passion on chosen subject(s), continue learning
    Cons - potential difficulty in finding students or marketing services effectively
  
4. Social media manager/community manager 

  Pro's: potentially well-paid  
Fun and interactive means of working 
 Opportunities for remote-working/self-employment     

Cons : dealing with negative feedback can be challenging  

5.SEO consultant/content markerter :
Pro's High demand 
Potential for significant earnings based on results delivered        
 Cons : rapidly changing nature (e.g., Google algorithms)   
6.Graphic designer ,
Pros Creative outlet , Can be self-taught using online resources,
Cons : Need intimate knowledge of several complex design programs.
